# govirt Requirements

## Overview

`govirt` is a unified CLI tool for provisioning VMs locally (libvirt + virt-install + cloud-init) or in the cloud (AWS EC2, DigitalOcean), using a single JSON config file and a standard cloud-init YAML.

It replicates all functionality of [goloo](https://github.com/emergingrobotics/goloo) вЂ” same commands, same config schema, same cloud-init variable substitution, same cloud provider support вЂ” with the local VM backend replaced from Canonical Multipass to libvirt/KVM.

---

## The Problem

Same as goloo: you want identical server environments locally and in the cloud, from one config. The difference is that govirt targets systems where libvirt/KVM is the preferred local hypervisor (Linux hosts, servers, CI environments) rather than Multipass.

---

## Solution

```bash
govirt create devbox              # Local VM via libvirt/KVM
govirt create devbox --aws        # AWS EC2 instance
govirt create devbox --do         # DigitalOcean Droplet
```

Same config file, same cloud-init YAML, same commands вЂ” only the local backend differs.

---

## Commands

```
govirt create <name>             Create a local VM (libvirt)
govirt create <name> --aws       Create an AWS EC2 instance
govirt create <name> --do        Create a DigitalOcean Droplet
govirt destroy <name>            Destroy VM (auto-detects provider)
govirt list                      List local VMs
govirt list --aws                List AWS VMs
govirt list --do                 List DigitalOcean Droplets
govirt ssh <name>                SSH into VM
govirt status <name>             Show VM status
govirt stop <name>               Stop VM (graceful shutdown)
govirt start <name>              Start VM
govirt dns swap <name>           Update DNS records to current VM IP (AWS and DigitalOcean)
```

### Flags

| Flag | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `--aws` | Use AWS provider |
| `--do`, `--digitalocean` | Use DigitalOcean provider |
| `--local` | Use local libvirt provider |
| `--dir PATH` | govirt config directory (default: `~/.config/govirt`); stacks at `<dir>/stacks/` |
| `--folder`, `-f PATH` | Full path to stacks folder (overrides `--dir`) |
| `--users`, `-u USERS` | GitHub usernames for SSH key injection (comma-separated) |
| `--verbose`, `-v` | Show detailed progress |
| `--no-hosts` | Skip /etc/hosts management for local VMs |
| `--version` | Show version |
| `--help`, `-h` | Show help |

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `GOVIRT_STACK_FOLDER` | Default base folder for configs (overridden by `--folder`/`-f`) |
| `DIGITALOCEAN_TOKEN` | DigitalOcean API token (required when using `--do`) |
| `GOVIRT_IMAGE_CACHE` | Directory to cache cloud images (default: `~/.cache/govirt/images`) |
| `LIBVIRT_DEFAULT_URI` | Libvirt connection URI (default: `qemu:///system`) |

