## Cloud-Init Processing

Identical to goloo вЂ” no changes.

### Variable Substitution

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `${SSH_PUBLIC_KEY}` | SSH public keys of the first user (fetched from GitHub) |
| `${SSH_PUBLIC_KEY_<USERNAME>}` | SSH public keys for a specific user (uppercase username) |

Keys fetched from `https://github.com/<username>.keys`.

Go template syntax (`{{ .Field }}`) is also supported when the cloud-init YAML contains `{{`.

### Mount Injection

When `vm.mounts` is non-empty, govirt appends to the processed cloud-init YAML:

```yaml
runcmd:
  - mkdir -p /home/ubuntu/code
  - mount -t virtiofs home-ubuntu-code /home/ubuntu/code

write_files:
  - path: /etc/fstab
    append: true
    content: |
      home-ubuntu-code   /home/ubuntu/code   virtiofs   defaults   0   0
```

This injection happens after user variable substitution, before writing the temp file.

