## LibvirtProvider: Create Sequence

1. Validate `vm.name`, `vm.users`, `vm.cpus`, `vm.memory`, `vm.disk`, `vm.image`
2. Resolve and download cloud image if not cached (`internal/images`)
3. Create CoW qcow2 overlay disk from cached image
4. Resize disk to `vm.disk` if larger than base image
5. Generate cloud-init NoCloud ISO (meta-data + processed user-data)
   - meta-data: `instance-id: govirt-<name>`, `local-hostname: <name>`
   - user-data: the `cloudInitPath` argument (already processed by caller)
6. If `vm.mounts` is non-empty, inject mount runcmd into a temporary modified cloud-init file and regenerate the ISO
7. Build and execute `virt-install` command
8. Poll for IP via `virsh domifaddr` (up to 60s, every 2s)
9. Populate `cfg.Local` with all state fields
10. Return (caller saves state)

---

## LibvirtProvider: Delete Sequence

1. Force-stop domain if running: `virsh destroy <name>` (ignore errors if already stopped)
2. Undefine domain and remove storage: `virsh undefine <name> --remove-all-storage`
3. Remove cloud-init ISO: `os.Remove(cfg.Local.CloudInitISO)`
4. Set `cfg.Local = nil`
5. Return

