## Security Considerations

1. SSH keys fetched from GitHub over HTTPS only
2. AWS credentials use standard AWS credential chain
3. `config.json` files may contain sensitive state вЂ” gitignore by default
4. Cloud-init ISO contains SSH public keys вЂ” store with mode 0600
5. VM disk files: follow libvirt storage pool permissions (typically `root:libvirt-qemu`)
6. `sudo tee` used for `/etc/hosts` management вЂ” same as goloo
7. DigitalOcean token never written to disk or logged

